ASSIGNMENT #1 (Group):  Communication Covenant due January 11
	 
	A Communication Covenant is an agreement every member of a team makes about communicating: 
	·  	promising to communicate regularly (even when the news is bad),
	·  	promising to answer your email how many times a day,
	·  	agreeing that you will be using Google Docs for file management,
	·  	specifying when and where your meetings are (1-2 times a week),
	·  	promising to notify team mates if you can’t make a meeting,
	·  	agreeing to reasonable punishments if a team mate is late or misses without notifying everyone,
	·  	promising to volunteer to do things and to do them well and on time. 
	 
	Include a table of preferred email addresses and cell phone numbers.  Title the file TEAMNAMEContacts
	 
	Put this file in the Google Docs folder your team is sharing with us.

Communication Covenant-Due Friday 11th 2013
Communication methods
Email - Email will be checked and acknowledged at least once every 24 hours by each member of team Overkill.
Calling- Calling/texting will be reserved to resolve urgent matters or if one team member cannot be reached by email.

Meetings
Tuesdays and Fridays at 7pm
Bi-weekly mandatory meetings - The Team has decided to meet twice a week on Tuesdays at 7:00pm and Fridays at 7:00pm.  
Although we will meet twice a week, additional meetings may be agreed upon by the group.
These meetings are mandatory.  Any team member that doesn’t attend will be subject to a penalty.
First infraction:  Jog around ring road once.
Second infraction:  Bring beverages for the group from Java City.
Three or more infractions:  They must sing a silly song in front of the entire class.

Code of Conduct
Disagreements are to be decided civilly, using the guidelines taught in the course.
Work will be planned out ahead of time. If you cannot meet your goal, you are required to explain why at least 3 days before it is due, and give a reason. Emergency reasons must be documented. If the reason is not acceptable, you will have to explain it in a meeting and will be warned not to do it that way again--otherwise you may be punished.
If response is needed, it should be noted in the email/document. If it is not received, a phone call should be tried. If, after that, a whole day still goes by, then the member can be considered AWOL.
Every team member’s Idea will be heard and thoughtfully considered by the group.
The two(or more) mandatory weekly meetings must be attended by all members. Notify if you are running late, or will not be present at least a day in advance. Will need a good excuse for missing the meeting.

Team OverKill’s Communication Covenant
Communication methods
Email - Email will be checked and acknowledged at least once every 24 hours by each member of team Overkill.
Calling- Calling/texting will be reserved to resolve urgent matters or if one team member cannot be reached by email.
All communications will be shared with every member of the group.
Meetings
Tuesdays and Fridays at 7pm
Bi-weekly mandatory meetings - The Team has decided to meet twice a week on Tuesdays and Fridays at 7:00pm, at the tables by the Engineering Tower/ICS building, or in the lab inside the ICS building in case of bad weather.
Although we will meet twice a week, additional meetings may be agreed upon by the group.
These meetings are mandatory.  Any team member that doesn’t attend will be subject to a penalty.
First infraction:  Jog around ring road once.
Second infraction:  Bring beverages for the group from Java City.
Three or more infractions:  They must sing a silly song in front of the entire class.
Code of Conduct
Disagreements are to be decided civilly, using the guidelines taught in the course.
All necessary information will be shared--even bad news.
Work will be planned out ahead of time. If you cannot meet your goal, you are required to explain why at least 3 days before it is due, and give a reason. Emergency reasons must be documented. If the reason is not acceptable, you will have to explain it in a meeting and will be warned not to do it that way again--otherwise you may be punished.
Work will be done well, on time, and on the Google Docs.
If response is needed, it should be noted in the email/document. If it is not received, a phone call should be tried. If, after that, a whole day still goes by, then the member can be considered AWOL.
Every team member’s Idea will be heard and thoughtfully considered by the group.
The two(or more) mandatory weekly meetings must be attended by all members. Notify if you are running late, or will not be present at least a day in advance. Will need a good excuse for missing the meeting
Every team member will fully communicate all project information to the entire group immediately as soon as it is known, no matter how bad or good it is.  .
Roles
Responsibilities such as project manager, note taker, and other jobs will be designated to a different team member at the beginning of every assignment to ensure we all have a taste of what all the roles have to offer.
